  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kanyemba Community Managed Disaster Risk Reduction Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve the resilience capacity of communities in Kanyemba to prepare,  plan, respond, manage and recover from future shocks and hazards. This will be achieved through; training a resilience committee on DRR, creating a hazard profile for Kanyemba Ward 1, conducting a simulation exercise, training people on adult literacy, running two village social events on DRR, and creating a computer-generated map of Kanyemba ward.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We will be training a resilience committee on DRR as well as creating a hazard profile for Kanyemba Ward 1.
Additionally, we will be conducting a simulation exercise, training 120 people on adult literacy, running two social events around DRR, and creating a CGI map of Kanyemba ward.</narrative>
  </description>
